   {:e #blake3 "379e2dab09383b2b0ffe76bf660339db703fef7a56d843c0e77b9fc2c25f2244" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: DS1-DS5 are individual components. DS6 wires them together into the unified daemon architecture and renames store.bin → checkpoint.bin. APPROACH: (1) RENAME: store.bin → checkpoint.bin in all code paths. .cache/store.bin → .cache/checkpoint.bin. Update layout.rs (read_slim_cache, write_slim_cache), live_store.rs (open, flush), daemon.rs (shutdown). Semantic change: checkpoint is a daemon recovery artifact, not a shared cache. (2) DAEMON STARTUP: serve_daemon() creates: WalWriter, CommitThread (with mpsc channel), CheckpointThread, ThreadPool. Wires them together. (3) DAEMON SHUTDOWN: FULL checkpoint → all WAL entries flushed to .edn. Write checkpoint.bin. Truncate WAL. Clean shutdown. (4) WRITE DISPATCH: handle_connection routes write tools to CommitThread via channel. Read tools execute directly with read lock. (5) .GITIGNORE: Add wal.bin and checkpoint.bin to .braid/.gitignore (they are local/ephemeral — .edn files are git-tracked). ACCEPTANCE: (1) Full daemon lifecycle: start → 100 writes → 50 reads → shutdown → restart → all data present. (2) grep store.bin crates/ returns 0 matches (fully renamed). (3) .braid/.gitignore includes wal.bin and checkpoint.bin. (4) WAL file exists during daemon run, does not exist after clean shutdown (truncated). FILES: daemon.rs (~200 LOC refactor), layout.rs (rename ~20 LOC), live_store.rs (rename ~10 LOC), .gitignore (~2 lines)." :op :assert}
